tem-spacing\">Chapter Guide</caption>\n\t\n\t<tbody>\n\t<tr>\n\t\n\t\t<td class=\"pi-horizontal-group-item pi-data-value pi-font pi-border-color pi-item-spacing\" data-source=\"previous\">← <a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_100\" title=\"Chapter 100\">Chapter 100</a></td>\n\t\n\t\t<td class=\"pi-horizontal-group-item pi-data-value pi-font pi-border-color pi-item-spacing\" data-source=\"next\"><a href=\"/wiki/Chapter_102\" title=\"Chapter 102\">Chapter 102</a> →</td>\n\t\n\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n</section>\n<nav class=\"pi-navigation pi-item-spacing pi-secondary-background pi-secondary-font\"><a href=\"/wiki/Category:Chapter_101_Images\" title=\"Category:Chapter 101 Images\">Chapter 101 Images</a></nav>\n</aside>\n\n<b>A Secret</b><span style=\"font-weight: normal\"> (<span class=\"t_nihongo_kanji\" lang=\"ja\"><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">内</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>ない</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">緒</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>しょ</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby><ruby lang=\"ja\"><rb style=\"text-justify:inter-word\">話</rb><rp> (</rp><rt>ばなし</rt><rp>) </rp></ruby></span><span class=\"t_nihongo_comma\" style=\"display:none\">,</span> <i><span class=\"t_nihongo_romaji\">Naisho-banashi</span></i><span class=\"t_nihongo_help\"><sup><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Installing_Japanese_character_sets\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Help:Installing Japanese character sets\"><span class=\"t_nihongo_icon\" style=\"color:#198975;font:bold 80% sans-serif;text-decoration:none;padding:0 .1em;\">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> is the one hundred and first chapter of <a href=\"/wiki/Koyoharu_Got%C5%8Dge\" title=\"Koyoharu Gotōge\">Koyoharu Gotōge's</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Kimetsu_no_Yaiba_(Manga)\" title=\"Kimetsu no Yaiba (Manga)\">Kimetsu no Yaiba</a>.\n<p></p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Summary\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Summary</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Characters_in_Order_of_Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Characters in Order of Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Events</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Navigation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Navigation</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Summary\">Summary</span></h2>\n<p>After arriving at the <a href=\"/wiki/Swordsmith_Village\" title=\"Swordsmith Village\">Swordsmith Village</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Tanjiro_Kamado\" title=\"Tanjiro Kamado\">Tanjiro</a> is greeted by the village’s chief, <a href=\"/wiki/Tecchin_Tecchikawahara\" title=\"Tecchin Tecchikawahara\">Tecchin Tecchikawahara</a>, who dubs himself the best of his craft in the village, and Tanjiro bows down before him at his request. Tecchin discloses to Tanjiro that the village is currently looking for <a href=\"/wiki/Hotaru_Haganezuka\" title=\"Hotaru Haganezuka\">Hotaru Haganezuka</a> after he disappeared a few days prior. Tanjiro comments on his swordsmith’s \"cute\" name, which Tecchin reveals that he himself gave him that name, but Hotaru strongly dislikes it. The chief notes about how Hotaru had always had a bad temper and when Tanjiro attempts to apologize for fueling this temper through breaking his swords, Tecchin refutes it by stressing Hotaru should be making a sword that wouldn’t break. He reassures Tanjiro that they will bring Hotaru back, or, alternatively, have a different swordsmith forge his new blade. The two part with Tecchin suggesting Tanjiro relax in the hot springs.\n</p>\n<figure class=\"thumb tleft show-info-icon\" style=\"width: 182px\"> \t<a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/1/13/Genya_after.png/revision/latest?cb=20200111020500\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/Genya_after.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"180\" height=\"246\" class=\"thumbimage\"></a> \t \t<figcaption class=\"thumbcaption\"> \t\t \t\t\t<a href=\"/wiki/File:Genya_after.png\" class=\"info-icon\"><svg><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-info-small\"></use></svg></a> \t\t \t\t \t\t \t\t\t<p class=\"caption\">Genya at the hot springs.</p> \t\t \t</figcaption> </figure>\n<p>While advancing to the springs, Tanjiro runs into <a href=\"/wiki/Mitsuri_Kanroji\" title=\"Mitsuri Kanroji\">Mitsuri Kanroji</a>, who had just returned from bathing. The <a href=\"/wiki/Love_Breathing\" title=\"Love Breathing\">Love</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Hashira\" title=\"Hashira\">Hashira</a> complains about how she was ignored when she asked for an individual’s name at the spring, upset about the disrespect. Tanjiro calms her by revealing that the villagers were almost done with the dinner for their guests, which Mitsuri excitedly hurries off to.\n</p><p>At the springs, Tanjiro is suddenly hit with a tooth and is surprised to encounter <a href=\"/wiki/Genya_Shinazugawa\" title=\"Genya Shinazugawa\">Genya Shinazugawa</a>. He excitedly jumps in the water and tries to converse with his fellow <a href=\"/wiki/Demon_Slayer_Corps\" title=\"Demon Slayer Corps\">Demon Slayer</a>, but is saddened after Genya angrily strikes him and storms off.\n</p>\n<figure class=\"thumb tright show-info-icon\" style=\"width: 202px\"> \t<a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/a/a8/Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png/revision/latest?cb=20190711150916\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"201\" class=\"thumbimage lazyload\"></a> \t<noscript><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/a/a8/Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png/revision/latest?cb=20190711150916\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/a/a8/Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/200?cb=20190711150916\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"201\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-image-name=\"Mitsuri playing with Nezuko CH101.png\" data-image-key=\"Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/a/a8/Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/200?cb=20190711150916\" /></a></noscript> \t<figcaption class=\"thumbcaption\"> \t\t \t\t\t<a href=\"/wiki/File:Mitsuri_playing_with_Nezuko_CH101.png\" class=\"info-icon\"><svg><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-info-small\"></use></svg></a> \t\t \t\t \t\t \t\t\t<p class=\"caption\">Mitsuri playing with Nezuko.</p> \t\t \t</figcaption> </figure>\n<p>Back at the village, Tanjiro praises Mitsuri for the amount she is capable of eating, declaring that he himself would also try to eat lots and grow strong. He then brings up Genya, with Mitsuri sadly observing how the boy must be <a href=\"/wiki/Sanemi_Shinazugawa\" title=\"Sanemi Shinazugawa\">Sanemi Shinazugawa</a>’s younger brother given that they share a last name, despite the <a href=\"/wiki/Wind_Breathing\" title=\"Wind Breathing\">Wind</a> Hashira telling her he didn’t have one. Tanjiro asks why she felt it was pitiful, and, while playing with <a href=\"/wiki/Nezuko_Kamado\" title=\"Nezuko Kamado\">Nezuko</a>, Mitsuri replies that she herself had five younger siblings and had good relationships with them. The two chat and both hope to someday be able to have a nice conversation with Genya, and Tanjiro decides to bring him leftovers since he didn’t come to dinner.\n</p><p>As they walk through a corridor with Nezuko, Tanjiro inquires Mitsuri on the reason why she joined the Demon Slayer Corps. Embarrassed, she states that she wanted to find a man to marry, someone who was stronger than her and could protect her. As she goes on about her thoughts, Tanjiro listens to her in disbelief.\n</p>\n<figure class=\"thumb tleft show-info-icon\" style=\"width: 202px\"> \t<a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/9/9d/Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png/revision/latest?cb=20190711150841\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"179\" class=\"thumbimage lazyload\"></a> \t<noscript><a href=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/9/9d/Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png/revision/latest?cb=20190711150841\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/9/9d/Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/200?cb=20190711150841\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"179\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-image-name=\"Mitsuri whispering to Tanjiro CH101.png\" data-image-key=\"Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/kimetsu-no-yaiba/images/9/9d/Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/200?cb=20190711150841\" /></a></noscript> \t<figcaption class=\"thumbcaption\"> \t\t \t\t\t<a href=\"/wiki/File:Mitsuri_whispering_to_Tanjiro_CH101.png\" class=\"info-icon\"><svg><use xlink:href=\"#wds-icons-info-small\"></use></svg></a> \t\t \t\t \t\t \t\t\t<p class=\"caption\">Mitsuri whispering to Tanjiro about the secret weapon.</p> \t\t \t</figcaption> </figure>\n<p>The trio are approached by a <a href=\"/wiki/Kakushi\" title=\"Kakushi\">Kakushi</a>, who informs Mitsuri that her new sword would be ready soon and that Mitsuri should check it out so that it could be adjusted if necessary. The Hashira bids farewell to Tanjiro and praises him for his hard work, expressing her approval for the siblings. After Tanjiro declares that he will be sure to defeat <a href=\"/wiki/Muzan_Kibutsuji\" title=\"Muzan Kibutsuji\">Muzan</a>, Mitsuri happily hints about a 'secret weapon' hidden in the village that could make him stronger.\n</p><p>The next day, Tanjiro searches through the forest looking for Hotaru and ponders about the secret weapon Mitsuri told him about. In the distance, he suddenly sees two individuals, one of them being the <a href=\"/wiki/Mist_Breathing\" title=\"Mist Breathing\">Mist</a> Hashira, <a href=\"/wiki/Muichiro_Tokito\" title=\"Muichiro Tokito\">Muichiro Tokito</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Characters_in_Order_of_Appearance\">Characters in Order of Appearance</span></h2>\n<div style=\"width:auto; height:190px; overflow:auto; margin-bottom:3px; padding-left:0.5em; border:1px solid #AAAAAA; -moz-border-radius-topleft:0.5em; -webkit-border-top-left-radius:0.5em; border-top-left-radius:0.5em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Tecchin_Tecchikawahara\" title=\"Tecchin Tecchikawahara\">Tecchin Tecchikawahara</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tanjiro_Kamado\" title=\"Tanjiro Kamado\">Tanjiro Kamado</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Mitsuri_Kanroji\" title=\"Mitsuri Kanroji\">Mitsuri Kanroji</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Genya_Shinazugawa\" title=\"Genya Shinazugawa\">Genya Shinazugawa</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Naho_Takada\" title=\"Naho Takada\">Naho Takada</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Nezuko_Kamado\" title=\"Nezuko Kamado\">Nezuko Kamado</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kotetsu\" title=\"Kotetsu\">Kotetsu</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Muichiro_Tokito\" title=\"Muichiro Tokito\">Muichiro Tokito</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Events\">Events</span></h2>\n<ul><li>Tanjiro meets with the village chief, Tecchin.</li>\n<li>Tanjiro encounters Mitsuri, the Love Hashira.</li>\n<li>Tanjiro encounters Genya.</li>\n<li>Mitsuri reveals a 'secret weapon' to Tanjiro.</li>\n<li>Tanjiro encounters Muichiro, the Mist Hashira.</li></ul>\n\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20210108110253\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.206 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.224 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 9310/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 168834/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 78100/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 28/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  133.820      1 -total\n 76.40%  102.232      1 Template:Manga_Navigation\n 73.77%   98.714      1 Template:Navibox\n 45.51%   60.905     26 Template:Navibox/info\n 39.51%   52.868     26 Template:Element_List\n 17.95%   24.017      1 Template:Chapter_Infobox\n 13.03%   17.437     26 Template:Force_Font_Color\n  3.08%    4.127      1 Template:Nihongo\n  2.38%    3.182      1 Template:Scroll_box\n  1.18%    1.575      3 Template:Ruby\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key prod:kimetsunoyaiba:pcache:idhash:834-0!canonical and timestamp 20210108110253 and revision id 75555\n -->\n</div>"}